{"lemma":"واضِحٌ","slug":"واضِحٌ","root":"#.ض.ح","root_slug":"_-ض-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ض-ح","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n42024"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B6%D9%90%D8%AD%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"clear"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"distinct"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"obvious"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"evident"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"plain"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of وَضَحَ (waḍaḥa, “to be clear, to appear”)."},"ipa":["/waː.dˤiħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n42024","headword_ar":"وَاضِحٌ","root":"wDH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waD~aAHN","text_ar":"وَضَّاحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but the latter has an intensive signification]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Apparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plainly apparent; overt; conspicuous; manifest; notorious; plain; obvious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evident;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unobscured; exposed to view; displayed; laid open; disclosed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uncovered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(So accord. to the explanation of the verb in the Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Perspicuous"},{"kind":"text","text":"language. (The Lexicons passim.) ―         -b3-  Also the ↓ latter, A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fair, and beautiful, complexion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of beautiful and smiling countenance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b4-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutawaD~iHN","text_ar":"مُتَوَضِّحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  Also the ↓ latter, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leprous."},{"kind":"text","text":"Hence Jedheemeh El-Abrash was called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaD~aAHu","text_ar":"الوَضَّاحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b6-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaD~aAHu","text_ar":"الوَضَّاحُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) The night is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahomaAnu","text_ar":"الدَّهْمَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b7-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bikoru AlwaD~aAHi","text_ar":"بِكْرُ الوَضَّاحِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The prayer of morning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"daybreak."},{"kind":"text","text":"The prayer of nightfall is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vinoYu dahomaAna","text_ar":"ثِنْىُ دَهْمَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, K [but in the CK and a MS. copy of the K, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahomaAna","text_ar":"دَهْمَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duhomaAna","text_ar":"دُهْمَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"].) ―         -b8-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZomu waD~aAHK","text_ar":"عَظْمُ وَضَّاحٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuZayomu","text_ar":"عُظَيْمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waD~aAHK","text_ar":"وَضَّاحٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain game"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the children of the Arabs of the desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which children take a white bone and throw it in the darkness of night, and then disperse themselves in search of it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who finds it wins."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) [See more in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EZm","text_ar":"عظم"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b9-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa minoka A^adonaY waADiHapK","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنْكَ اَدْنَى وَاضِحَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is plainly apparent to thee, as though he had become white."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN waADHu AlHasabi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ وَاضحُ الحَسَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waD~aAHuhu","text_ar":"وَضَّاحُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man as though he were conspicuous, clean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pure, and white, with respect to rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality, nobility, reputation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b11-  In like manner one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu Aln~asabu AlwaD~aAHu","text_ar":"لَهُ النَّسَبُ الوَضَّاحُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is of conspicuous and pure race,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lineage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waADiHN","text_ar":"وَاضِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  An"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"illustrious"},{"kind":"text","text":"man. (EsSaadee.) ―         -b13-  [And so]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"min Aln~aAsi waA^awobaA$N","text_ar":"مِن النَّاسِ وَاَوْبَاشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoDaAHN","text_ar":"اَوْضَاحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Illustrious people, and mixed people of the baser sort;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"companies of people of various tribes."},{"kind":"text","text":"No sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AwDAH","text_ar":"اوضاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense has been heard. (L.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwuD~axu","text_ar":"الوُضَّخُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waADiHN","text_ar":"وَاضِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The stars called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkawaAkibu","text_ar":"الكَوَاكِبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxun~asu","text_ar":"الخُنَّسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Saturn, Jupiter, Mars, Venus, and Mercury,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when in conjunction with the bright stars of the Mansions of the Moon."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}